        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 20 at 6:08AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 607 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Mulberry, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Jethro...                         Mulberry...
Cass...                           Barnes...
Redding...                        Watalula...
Toney...                          Turners Bend...
Cecil...                          Lonelm...
Taft...                           Ozark...
Cravens...                        Paradise...
Dyer...                           Wiederkehr Village...

This includes Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 18 and
38.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
